@*
    This NavMenu component uses custom CSS classes defined in the .razor.css file for styling navigation items.
    - The "nav-item" class is added to handle CSS changes based on the active state determined by the NavLink component.
    - The current item is styled using the ".nav-item ::deep a.active" selector to apply "background-color: #1f2937" and "color: white" to indicate it is active.
    - The default state of other items is styled similarly to "text-gray-400" for a muted appearance,
      and on hover, they change to "hover:text-white hover:bg-gray-800" for better visibility.
    - For simplicity, <li> tags have been replaced with <div> tags to manage the navigation structure.

    NavMenu.razor Functionality:
    - The NavMenu component is used in both mobile and desktop views.
    - It accepts an 'IsMobileView' parameter to differentiate between contexts.

    Mobile View (MobileSidebar):
    - IsMobileView is set to true.
    - Clicking a NavLink triggers the OnSidebarClose event.
    - This closes the mobile sidebar after navigation.

    Desktop View:
    - IsMobileView is set to false.
    - Clicking a NavLink does not trigger any additional logic.
    - The sidebar remains static and always visible.

    This approach ensures efficient behavior in both contexts:
    - Mobile: Provides necessary sidebar closing functionality.
    - Desktop: Avoids unnecessary operations, as the sidebar is always visible.
*@

